WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.592 --> 00:00:10.928
<i>- Baran. is this you?</i>

2
00:00:16.433 --> 00:00:19.144
- It began after a bad case
of viral meningitis

3
00:00:19.228 --> 00:00:20.896
when I was five.

4
00:00:20.979 --> 00:00:23.232
They tried every
anti-seizure medication.

5
00:00:23.315 --> 00:00:27.194
but I still had episodes
every few months or so.

6
00:00:27.277 --> 00:00:28.445
No one's ever noticed before.

7
00:00:28.529 --> 00:00:29.988
They just think I'm thoughtful.

8
00:00:32.032 --> 00:00:33.367
- Are you driving?

9
00:00:33.450 --> 00:00:36.495
- I couldn't
until laser ablation

10
00:00:36.578 --> 00:00:39.831
to my left temporal lobe
12 years ago.

11
00:00:39.915 --> 00:00:42.668
Between that and the Keppra.
I've been seizure-free.

12
00:00:42.709 --> 00:00:46.380
cleared by Neurology to drive
and to work as an attending.

13
00:00:48.173 --> 00:00:50.384
- How long. uh.
between the seizure

14
00:00:50.467 --> 00:00:52.261
you had today and the last one?

15
00:00:52.344 --> 00:00:55.597
- It's been well over a year.

16
00:00:57.766 --> 00:00:59.268
But I had two today.

17
00:01:03.897 --> 00:01:05.357
I don't know why.

18
00:01:05.440 --> 00:01:08.569
It could be sleep deprivation.
new job stress.

19
00:01:08.652 --> 00:01:11.863
I--I haven't had to deal
with Peds cases

20
00:01:11.947 --> 00:01:13.407
since Afghanistan.

21
00:01:13.448 --> 00:01:15.117
- What are your options now?

22
00:01:15.200 --> 00:01:17.244
- Um...

23
00:01:17.327 --> 00:01:20.789
up my Keppra or maybe try

24
00:01:20.872 --> 00:01:22.416
one of the newer
anti-seizure meds.

25
00:01:22.499 --> 00:01:25.252
But if that doesn't work.
I'm left with two choices--

26
00:01:25.335 --> 00:01:29.715
um. a temporal lobectomy.
which could impair my speech.

27
00:01:29.798 --> 00:01:32.175
or get a neuromodulation
device.

28
00:01:32.259 --> 00:01:33.927
which can sense
and stop the seizures

29
00:01:33.969 --> 00:01:35.762
almost immediately.

30
00:01:35.804 --> 00:01:37.598
- You need to disclose this.

31
00:01:37.639 --> 00:01:39.600
- I know. I have a plan.

32
00:01:39.683 --> 00:01:40.726
- Hey. Robby.
Dana's looking for you.

33
00:01:40.809 --> 00:01:41.935
She's in Peds.

34
00:01:42.019 --> 00:01:43.270
- Yeah. OK.
I'll be right there.

35
00:01:43.353 --> 00:01:44.646
[door closes]

36
00:01:44.730 --> 00:01:45.897
- Sounds like
you're needed in Peds.

37
00:01:45.981 --> 00:01:47.983
and I have patients to see.

38
00:01:48.066 --> 00:01:49.943
- Robby. pregnant woman
with severe headache

39
00:01:49.985 --> 00:01:51.612
on her way in by ambulance.

40
00:01:51.695 --> 00:01:54.197
- Find Abbot
or a night shift resident.

41
00:02:00.787 --> 00:02:03.832
{\an8}[indistinct chatter]

42
00:02:09.212 --> 00:02:11.089
- Need you to turn out
your pockets.

43
00:02:17.346 --> 00:02:19.222
OK. Show me your hands.

44
00:02:39.368 --> 00:02:40.869
- [sighs]

45
00:02:43.747 --> 00:02:47.125
[urine trickling]

46
00:02:47.209 --> 00:02:48.543
Come here often?

47
00:02:52.255 --> 00:02:54.007
[baby crying]

48
00:02:54.049 --> 00:02:55.550
- [clears throat]

49
00:02:57.302 --> 00:02:58.720
What's going on?

50
00:02:58.804 --> 00:03:00.514
- Oh. sorry--false alarm.

51
00:03:00.555 --> 00:03:02.683
We thought she spiked a fever.
but it was the wrong chart

52
00:03:02.766 --> 00:03:05.143
from our analog hell.

53
00:03:05.227 --> 00:03:07.688
You know anybody who might
consider kinship adoption?

54
00:03:07.771 --> 00:03:09.481
Doctors and nurses qualify.

55
00:03:09.564 --> 00:03:11.108
- Don't look at me.

56
00:03:11.191 --> 00:03:13.193
Hey. can your staff
keep an eye on Dr. Al-Hashimi

57
00:03:13.276 --> 00:03:14.277
until she leaves?

58
00:03:14.361 --> 00:03:16.697
- Why?

59
00:03:16.780 --> 00:03:18.865
- Uh. because I think
she's tired.

60
00:03:18.949 --> 00:03:20.492
and I don't want her
to make any mistakes.

61
00:03:20.534 --> 00:03:22.536
- Oh. great advice.
Maybe you should take it.

62
00:03:22.619 --> 00:03:23.829
- Yeah.

63
00:03:23.912 --> 00:03:25.247
I'm gonna go get
some fresh air.

64
00:03:25.330 --> 00:03:26.832
- Grab some for me
while you're out there.

65
00:03:26.873 --> 00:03:27.916
- Your lungs wouldn't know
what to do with it.

66
00:03:27.999 --> 00:03:29.000
- Screw you!

67
00:03:29.084 --> 00:03:30.627
- In front of the baby? Nice.

68
00:03:30.711 --> 00:03:33.505
[baby crying]

69
00:03:33.588 --> 00:03:35.132
- Yeah.

70
00:03:35.215 --> 00:03:37.008
- We are the night crawlers.

71
00:03:37.050 --> 00:03:39.970
We deal with the weirdest
and the wildest because...

72
00:03:40.053 --> 00:03:42.514
all: We are the weirdest
and the wildest of them all.

73
00:03:42.597 --> 00:03:43.640
- That is right. and tonight.

74
00:03:43.724 --> 00:03:44.975
they are really gonna be
crawling.

75
00:03:45.058 --> 00:03:46.351
Now go get some!

76
00:03:46.435 --> 00:03:47.394
all: Hooah!

77
00:03:47.436 --> 00:03:48.520
- [claps]

78
00:03:50.313 --> 00:03:51.773
- [clears throat]

79
00:03:51.857 --> 00:03:53.400
- Sorry to wake you.

80
00:03:53.442 --> 00:03:54.943
- I--I was thinking.

81
00:03:58.321 --> 00:04:00.031
[yawns] Doubt PTX.

82
00:04:00.115 --> 00:04:02.242
- You're supposed
to be leaving.

83
00:04:02.325 --> 00:04:03.452
- I am.

84
00:04:05.746 --> 00:04:07.247
- You know.
this spirit quest of yours

85
00:04:07.289 --> 00:04:09.082
has a lot of people
up in arms around here.

86
00:04:09.166 --> 00:04:10.584
- Everyone's gonna be fine
without me.

87
00:04:10.625 --> 00:04:12.210
and it's hardly a spirit quest.

88
00:04:12.294 --> 00:04:13.920
- Whatever it is.
it seems you've given people

89
00:04:13.962 --> 00:04:15.172
the impression
you might not be coming back.

90
00:04:15.255 --> 00:04:16.590
- Well. who knows

91
00:04:16.673 --> 00:04:18.091
what the future has in store
for any of us?

92
00:04:18.133 --> 00:04:19.426
- Yeah. saying shit
like that right there

93
00:04:19.509 --> 00:04:20.469
isn't helping.

94
00:04:20.552 --> 00:04:21.928
People are worried about you.

95
00:04:21.970 --> 00:04:23.805
- Dr. Abbot.
the patient in South 21.

96
00:04:23.889 --> 00:04:25.265
Digby. he's missing again.

97
00:04:25.348 --> 00:04:26.641
- Sounds like
a day shift problem.

98
00:04:26.725 --> 00:04:28.977
- Not if he was
handed off already.

99
00:04:33.148 --> 00:04:34.733
- Best I can do
under the circumstances.

100
00:04:34.816 --> 00:04:36.026
- Thank you.

101
00:04:36.109 --> 00:04:37.527
Hey. don't leave
before I get back. yeah?

102
00:04:37.611 --> 00:04:39.362
- Hell. I feel like
I live here now.

103
00:04:42.783 --> 00:04:44.034
- Your friend fixing your bike?

104
00:04:44.117 --> 00:04:45.285
- Ambulance clipped it

105
00:04:45.327 --> 00:04:47.120
while it was just
parked here today.

106
00:04:47.204 --> 00:04:49.331
- Jesus Christ.

107
00:04:49.414 --> 00:04:50.957
That's a sign
if I've ever seen one.

108
00:04:50.999 --> 00:04:52.501
[siren chirps]

109
00:04:52.584 --> 00:04:54.336
Yeah. here's the thing--
when people worry about you.

110
00:04:54.419 --> 00:04:56.129
it makes me think that
I should be worried about you.

111
00:04:56.171 --> 00:04:57.798
and I don't like worrying
about things.

112
00:04:57.839 --> 00:04:58.965
- Ooh. Now you're a shrink?

113
00:04:59.049 --> 00:05:00.091
- No. I'm trying
to be your friend.

114
00:05:00.175 --> 00:05:01.259
You got--you got Dana convinced

115
00:05:01.343 --> 00:05:03.011
that you're gonna
hurt yourself.

116
00:05:03.094 --> 00:05:04.596
- Dana's got her own issues.
- That sounds like projection.

117
00:05:04.679 --> 00:05:05.931
- Are you seriously trying
to have this fucking

118
00:05:06.014 --> 00:05:07.474
conversation with me
right now. man?

119
00:05:07.557 --> 00:05:09.100
I--I'm not the one

120
00:05:09.184 --> 00:05:11.478
who spends his free time
getting shot at.

121
00:05:11.520 --> 00:05:13.063
Hooah!

122
00:05:13.146 --> 00:05:15.398
- Hey. Dr. Robby.
this is Judith Lastrade--

123
00:05:15.482 --> 00:05:17.651
36 weeks pregnant
with two days of headache.

124
00:05:17.692 --> 00:05:20.153
now a 10 out of 10
with blurred vision.

125
00:05:20.195 --> 00:05:23.323
BP 174/120. heart rate 92.

126
00:05:23.406 --> 00:05:25.450
No relief with fentanyl.
- Judith. I'm Dr. Abbot.

127
00:05:25.534 --> 00:05:26.827
Any weakness
in your arms or legs?

128
00:05:26.910 --> 00:05:28.370
- No. no. Is this a stroke?

129
00:05:28.453 --> 00:05:29.788
- We need to check
for everything.

130
00:05:29.871 --> 00:05:32.499
- Pitting edema
with severe preeclampsia.

131
00:05:32.582 --> 00:05:34.459
Where are you doing
your prenatal care?

132
00:05:34.543 --> 00:05:35.669
- Nowhere.

133
00:05:35.752 --> 00:05:37.170
It's a wild pregnancy.

134
00:05:37.254 --> 00:05:39.214
I want a free birth.

135
00:05:41.341 --> 00:05:44.678
- This 81-year-old nun
presents with red. itchy eyes

136
00:05:44.719 --> 00:05:47.848
with secretions
for the past two days.

137
00:05:47.889 --> 00:05:50.350
Patient complains
of no URI symptoms.

138
00:05:50.392 --> 00:05:51.893
no contact with any chemical...
- Hey.

139
00:05:51.977 --> 00:05:53.311
- Agents.
no known exposures--

140
00:05:53.395 --> 00:05:54.855
- Want half a Monster?

141
00:05:54.896 --> 00:05:56.523
- Oh. no. thanks.

142
00:05:56.565 --> 00:05:58.024
I--I don't really want
to stay awake

143
00:05:58.066 --> 00:06:00.151
any longer than I have to.

144
00:06:00.235 --> 00:06:01.695
- Yeah. I hear you.

145
00:06:03.238 --> 00:06:05.198
- Did you find your ID badge?

146
00:06:05.282 --> 00:06:06.783
- Uh. no.

147
00:06:06.867 --> 00:06:09.035
You any closer to deciding
what's next for you?

148
00:06:09.119 --> 00:06:10.996
- Uh. yeah. I'm seriously
considering law school.

149
00:06:11.079 --> 00:06:12.497
- What?
What are you talking about?

150
00:06:12.581 --> 00:06:14.457
You're gonna be a great doctor.

151
00:06:15.917 --> 00:06:19.129
- I mean. no offense. but look
what this place does to you.

152
00:06:19.212 --> 00:06:20.797
Langdon's an addict.

153
00:06:20.881 --> 00:06:23.508
- Is a person with
a substance use disorder.

154
00:06:23.592 --> 00:06:25.427
- McKay was on house arrest.

155
00:06:25.510 --> 00:06:26.928
Dana's a time bomb.

156
00:06:27.012 --> 00:06:28.680
Santos is one
of the angriest people

157
00:06:28.763 --> 00:06:30.181
you are ever going to meet.

158
00:06:30.265 --> 00:06:31.683
- Sarcastic. yes.
Cynical. definitely.

159
00:06:31.766 --> 00:06:33.226
I don't know
if she's. you know--

160
00:06:33.268 --> 00:06:34.644
- Mel?

161
00:06:35.687 --> 00:06:38.648
Samira has no life.

162
00:06:38.732 --> 00:06:41.860
Abbot's an adrenaline junkie
who gets shot at for fun.

163
00:06:41.943 --> 00:06:44.738
Robby's got. like. PTSD
or something way fucking worse.

164
00:06:44.779 --> 00:06:45.989
- OK. well. I--I mean.

165
00:06:46.072 --> 00:06:48.116
I'd hate to know
what you think about me.

166
00:06:49.659 --> 00:06:51.244
- I don't know. I just--

167
00:06:51.328 --> 00:06:53.914
the more time I spend here.

168
00:06:53.955 --> 00:06:55.123
the more I realize
the importance

169
00:06:55.206 --> 00:06:57.876
of my mental health.

170
00:06:58.960 --> 00:06:59.961
- Mm.

171
00:07:00.045 --> 00:07:01.254
- For patients and for us.

172
00:07:01.338 --> 00:07:03.882
And this is...

173
00:07:03.965 --> 00:07:05.050
- Yeah.

174
00:07:05.133 --> 00:07:06.301
Well. you know.

175
00:07:06.384 --> 00:07:09.220
maybe that's
what you should focus on.

176
00:07:10.305 --> 00:07:12.515
- What?
- Mental health.

177
00:07:12.599 --> 00:07:14.768
Clearly. you have
a passion for it. right?

178
00:07:14.851 --> 00:07:16.353
I mean. that's--that's great.

179
00:07:16.436 --> 00:07:17.437
- I don't know if
I'd call it a passion.

180
00:07:17.479 --> 00:07:19.648
I would call it. like. a...

181
00:07:22.525 --> 00:07:24.152
Oh. my God.

182
00:07:26.029 --> 00:07:28.198
You might be right.

183
00:07:29.741 --> 00:07:31.284
Oh. you're a genius. Whitaker.

184
00:07:31.368 --> 00:07:32.494
- Oh. OK.

185
00:07:32.577 --> 00:07:34.120
[laughs]

186
00:07:34.204 --> 00:07:36.122
- CTG is on.

187
00:07:36.206 --> 00:07:38.458
- CTG?
- Cardiotocography.

188
00:07:38.500 --> 00:07:41.878
Measures the baby's heart rate
and checks for contractions.

189
00:07:41.962 --> 00:07:43.463
- Fetal heart rate 128.

190
00:07:43.505 --> 00:07:44.965
Normal range. Nazely?

191
00:07:45.048 --> 00:07:46.883
- 110 to 160.

192
00:07:46.967 --> 00:07:48.760
- So the baby's OK?

193
00:07:48.843 --> 00:07:49.970
- Right now. yes.

194
00:07:50.011 --> 00:07:51.388
128 is reassuring.

195
00:07:51.471 --> 00:07:53.598
- BP's 170/119.

196
00:07:53.682 --> 00:07:55.350
6 grams of magnesium
running in.

197
00:07:55.433 --> 00:07:56.977
- Your next move. Crus?

198
00:07:57.018 --> 00:07:59.604
- 20 of labetalol.
IV push over two minutes.

199
00:07:59.688 --> 00:08:01.147
- Uh. what's happening?

200
00:08:01.189 --> 00:08:03.149
- Uh. you have a condition
called preeclampsia.

201
00:08:03.233 --> 00:08:04.442
- And how did it happen?

202
00:08:04.526 --> 00:08:06.653
- Uh. nobody really knows.
actually.

203
00:08:06.736 --> 00:08:08.989
It affects about 10%
of the pregnancies.

204
00:08:09.072 --> 00:08:10.490
High blood pressure. headaches.

205
00:08:10.532 --> 00:08:12.951
protein in the urine.
and swollen ankles.

206
00:08:13.034 --> 00:08:15.245
- OK. well.
it's a wild pregnancy.

207
00:08:15.328 --> 00:08:17.455
so that means no medical care.

208
00:08:17.539 --> 00:08:19.499
- Then why are you here?

209
00:08:19.541 --> 00:08:20.959
- [crying]

210
00:08:21.042 --> 00:08:23.294
I just need to get rid
of this headache.

211
00:08:25.422 --> 00:08:28.383
- Well. if we don't lower
your blood pressure

212
00:08:28.466 --> 00:08:31.344
and treat with magnesium.
there can be problems.

213
00:08:31.386 --> 00:08:32.554
- Like what?

214
00:08:32.637 --> 00:08:34.180
- Seizures. bleeding.

215
00:08:34.264 --> 00:08:36.307
even death.
for you and the baby.

216
00:08:36.391 --> 00:08:38.143
- [crying] Oh. my God.

217
00:08:38.226 --> 00:08:39.853
- Robby. your VIP's
ready to go.

218
00:08:39.894 --> 00:08:41.896
- OK. I'll be right there.

219
00:08:41.980 --> 00:08:43.523
You good?
- Yeah. I'm good.

220
00:08:43.606 --> 00:08:46.234
I got it.
With my eyes closed.

221
00:08:46.317 --> 00:08:47.569
But I won't. Maybe one eye.

222
00:08:47.652 --> 00:08:48.903
[clicks tongue]

223
00:08:48.987 --> 00:08:50.030
Hey--
[door closes]

224
00:08:50.071 --> 00:08:52.073
[machines beeping]

225
00:08:53.450 --> 00:08:54.826
- Hey. Becca.
How you feeling?

226
00:08:54.909 --> 00:08:57.120
<i>- I'm better. Thanks.</i>

227
00:08:58.621 --> 00:08:59.956
- Where are you?

228
00:09:00.040 --> 00:09:01.875
<i>- I'm at Adam's house.</i>

229
00:09:01.916 --> 00:09:03.626
<i>Can I call you later?
We're watching a movie.</i>

230
00:09:03.710 --> 00:09:04.878
- Oh. sure.
I just--I thought

231
00:09:04.919 --> 00:09:06.379
you were gonna see
the fireworks.

232
00:09:06.463 --> 00:09:09.007
<i>- Nope. we decided
to watch "Elf" instead.</i>

233
00:09:09.090 --> 00:09:10.341
- Ah.

234
00:09:10.425 --> 00:09:12.343
Of course you did.
<i>- OK.</i>

235
00:09:12.427 --> 00:09:14.054
<i>I'll call you tomorrow!</i>
- Tomorrow? Wait.

236
00:09:14.095 --> 00:09:16.347
Uh. are--are you
spending the night?

237
00:09:16.431 --> 00:09:18.224
<i>- Um. uh. yes.</i>

238
00:09:18.266 --> 00:09:19.976
<i>His parents invited me.</i>

239
00:09:20.060 --> 00:09:21.478
- They--they need
to ask me that.

240
00:09:21.561 --> 00:09:23.897
<i>- Are--are you
staying here too?</i>

241
00:09:23.980 --> 00:09:27.984
- No. they--they needed to ask
if it was OK if you stayed.

242
00:09:28.068 --> 00:09:29.360
<i>- Why?</i>

243
00:09:29.444 --> 00:09:34.032
- Be--because. uh.
it's polite.

244
00:09:34.074 --> 00:09:36.284
It's the right--
it's the right thing to do.

245
00:09:36.367 --> 00:09:39.412
Um. I need to talk to them.

246
00:09:39.454 --> 00:09:42.082
<i>- Um. they're not here.
They're at a barbecue.</i>

247
00:09:42.165 --> 00:09:44.250
- OK. um.
can you have them call me

248
00:09:44.292 --> 00:09:45.585
as soon as they get home?

249
00:09:45.627 --> 00:09:47.420
<i>- Yes.</i>
- Can you promise?

250
00:09:47.504 --> 00:09:49.297
<i>- I promise.
OK. bye. Mel!</i>

251
00:09:49.380 --> 00:09:50.799
[phone chimes]
- Bye. Have fun--

252
00:09:52.175 --> 00:09:53.718
- Thanks for fixing my bike.

253
00:09:53.802 --> 00:09:55.970
- Well. you keep me running.
I'll keep her going.

254
00:09:57.847 --> 00:10:01.351
You know. the Cree don't have
a word for goodbye.

255
00:10:01.434 --> 00:10:02.519
- You know a lot of Cree?

256
00:10:02.602 --> 00:10:04.270
- [chuckles] A bit.

257
00:10:04.354 --> 00:10:05.438
I got around. man.

258
00:10:05.480 --> 00:10:06.815
- I don't doubt it.

259
00:10:09.317 --> 00:10:11.736
- Look. I'll come back
for all this other shit...

260
00:10:11.820 --> 00:10:13.113
- Great.

261
00:10:13.154 --> 00:10:14.572
- If you promise to come back

262
00:10:14.656 --> 00:10:16.449
and let me take
the Bonnie for a ride.

263
00:10:16.491 --> 00:10:17.617
- Uh. I don't know.

264
00:10:17.700 --> 00:10:19.035
I've seen you ride. old man.

265
00:10:19.119 --> 00:10:20.453
- Fuck you.

266
00:10:20.537 --> 00:10:22.413
I mean it.

267
00:10:22.497 --> 00:10:23.706
We got a deal?

268
00:10:26.793 --> 00:10:28.670
- I'll think about it.

269
00:10:41.766 --> 00:10:43.768
This looks like an ambush.

270
00:10:43.852 --> 00:10:45.436
- We got a slight hiccup
in chairs.

271
00:10:45.520 --> 00:10:46.479
- ICE is back?

272
00:10:46.563 --> 00:10:48.481
- No. we got a dead body.

273
00:10:48.565 --> 00:10:50.150
- Somebody died out there?
- Yeah.

274
00:10:50.191 --> 00:10:51.943
- Poor devil checked in
at 5:00 this morning.

275
00:10:52.026 --> 00:10:53.444
He was a DNR.
- [groans]

276
00:10:53.486 --> 00:10:54.612
What was his chief complaint?
- Hemorrhoids

277
00:10:54.696 --> 00:10:56.156
and constipation.
- No shit.

278
00:10:56.197 --> 00:10:58.491
- Hence the constipation.
- [laughs]

279
00:10:58.533 --> 00:11:00.201
- Throw me a slow one.
I'm gonna hit it.

280
00:11:00.285 --> 00:11:01.870
- Tell the night shift.
I'm saying that's when he died.

281
00:11:01.953 --> 00:11:03.163
We all in agreement on that?

282
00:11:03.204 --> 00:11:04.497
- To the grave.

283
00:11:04.581 --> 00:11:06.291
Just like poor Jasper.

284
00:11:06.374 --> 00:11:07.792
- You're on fire.

285
00:11:07.876 --> 00:11:09.294
- Just getting my second wind.

286
00:11:10.587 --> 00:11:11.796
- How's the headache?

287
00:11:11.880 --> 00:11:13.131
- Still a 10.

288
00:11:13.214 --> 00:11:14.632
- More fentanyl?

289
00:11:14.716 --> 00:11:17.010
- Yep.
- BP's good. Another 50.

290
00:11:17.093 --> 00:11:18.511
- Hey. Abbot.

291
00:11:18.553 --> 00:11:20.471
Attending and resident
are stuck in the OR.

292
00:11:20.555 --> 00:11:22.307
- Oh. you're
the next best thing.

293
00:11:22.390 --> 00:11:23.683
- Better. some would say.

294
00:11:23.725 --> 00:11:25.018
- Mm.

295
00:11:25.059 --> 00:11:26.519
- What do you got?
- This is Judith.

296
00:11:26.603 --> 00:11:29.022
G1. P0 with no prenatal care.

297
00:11:29.063 --> 00:11:31.107
Preeclampsia
with severe hypertension.

298
00:11:31.191 --> 00:11:33.526
- Hi. Judith.
Nurse Garvin from OB.

299
00:11:33.610 --> 00:11:34.986
- Some jelly on the belly.

300
00:11:35.069 --> 00:11:36.529
Gonna take a quick look
with ultrasound.

301
00:11:36.613 --> 00:11:38.489
- No. no. no.
Ultrasound can harm the baby.

302
00:11:38.573 --> 00:11:40.491
- Not true.
- Not doing the ultrasound

303
00:11:40.575 --> 00:11:42.660
could end up harming you
and the baby.

304
00:11:43.912 --> 00:11:45.038
- [sighs] OK.

305
00:11:45.079 --> 00:11:47.540
Just do it as fast as you can.

306
00:11:47.624 --> 00:11:50.084
- Why no prenatal care. Judith?

307
00:11:51.127 --> 00:11:53.504
- I wanted a free birth--

308
00:11:53.588 --> 00:11:55.673
no doctors. no hospital.
no medicine.

309
00:11:55.757 --> 00:11:58.509
- Mm. You have a midwife?

310
00:11:58.593 --> 00:11:59.552
A birth doula?

311
00:11:59.636 --> 00:12:02.013
- No. I don't need one.

312
00:12:02.055 --> 00:12:03.264
Women have been having
children on their own

313
00:12:03.348 --> 00:12:04.557
for thousands of years.

314
00:12:04.599 --> 00:12:06.059
- Yeah. with
an infant mortality rate

315
00:12:06.142 --> 00:12:08.978
of 30% for most of those
thousands of years.

316
00:12:09.062 --> 00:12:11.231
- Femur length 7 centimeters.
- 37 weeks.

317
00:12:11.314 --> 00:12:13.233
They'll probably induce.

318
00:12:13.274 --> 00:12:15.151
- What? No.

319
00:12:15.235 --> 00:12:16.527
No. no. no. no. Absolutely not.

320
00:12:16.611 --> 00:12:18.071
- At 37 weeks.

321
00:12:18.112 --> 00:12:20.240
the cure for preeclampsia
is to deliver the baby.

322
00:12:20.323 --> 00:12:22.075
We need to get you upstairs
so the OB doctors

323
00:12:22.116 --> 00:12:24.827
can induce labor
to save you and your baby.

324
00:12:24.911 --> 00:12:27.330
- No. No. no. no. no. Mm-mm.

325
00:12:29.666 --> 00:12:31.334
- Yep. that's
definitely Jasper.

326
00:12:31.417 --> 00:12:32.585
He was alive and kicking

327
00:12:32.669 --> 00:12:34.003
when my shift ended
this morning.

328
00:12:34.087 --> 00:12:35.380
This is definitely
a day shift patient.

329
00:12:35.463 --> 00:12:36.714
- Now he's not a patient.

330
00:12:36.798 --> 00:12:38.258
He's a DB that
we gotta deal with.

331
00:12:38.299 --> 00:12:39.467
- [sighs]

332
00:12:40.802 --> 00:12:41.970
- Is this dude dead?

333
00:12:42.053 --> 00:12:43.471
both: Nope.

334
00:12:43.554 --> 00:12:45.306
- All right. Mr. Reed.
time to take you back

335
00:12:45.390 --> 00:12:46.766
and get you checked out. OK?

336
00:12:46.849 --> 00:12:48.226
- He sure looks dead.
- Are you a doctor?

337
00:12:48.309 --> 00:12:50.561
- No. but he--
- Has hypernarcolepsy.

338
00:12:50.645 --> 00:12:52.272
It's no joke.
- Mm-hmm.

339
00:12:52.355 --> 00:12:54.565
- Excuse me.
- [clears throat]

340
00:12:54.649 --> 00:12:56.484
- Oh. sometimes I hate nights.

341
00:12:56.567 --> 00:12:57.777
- Yep.
- Oof.

342
00:12:57.819 --> 00:12:58.861
[grunts]

343
00:13:04.158 --> 00:13:07.203
[fireworks whistling. popping]

344
00:13:08.705 --> 00:13:10.039
- Wow.

345
00:13:10.123 --> 00:13:13.251
Crazy how muggy
it still is out here.

346
00:13:13.334 --> 00:13:15.962
You. uh--you seen Robby?

347
00:13:16.004 --> 00:13:18.131
- Uh. not for a bit.

348
00:13:18.172 --> 00:13:19.465
- You catch up on your charts

349
00:13:19.507 --> 00:13:20.967
from the beginning
of the shift?

350
00:13:21.009 --> 00:13:22.218
- Yeah.

351
00:13:22.302 --> 00:13:23.303
- What are you still
doing here?

352
00:13:23.344 --> 00:13:25.096
- Uh. just gonna...

353
00:13:25.179 --> 00:13:27.473
- You staying
for the fireworks?

354
00:13:27.557 --> 00:13:28.891
- Yeah.

355
00:13:28.975 --> 00:13:30.310
I was supposed to see them
with Becca.

356
00:13:30.351 --> 00:13:34.314
but she is
at her boyfriend Adam's

357
00:13:34.355 --> 00:13:36.232
family's house instead.

358
00:13:40.528 --> 00:13:46.659
- Your sister seems like
she's. uh. pretty put-together.

359
00:13:46.743 --> 00:13:47.994
- Yeah.

360
00:13:48.036 --> 00:13:50.788
Uh. a lot more than I realized.

361
00:13:52.707 --> 00:13:54.125
- How was your day?

362
00:13:55.960 --> 00:13:58.379
- I've had better.

363
00:13:58.463 --> 00:13:59.589
You?

364
00:14:02.467 --> 00:14:04.844
- Yeah.

365
00:14:04.886 --> 00:14:08.139
But then again.
I've had a lot worse.

366
00:14:08.222 --> 00:14:10.683
Hell. I did a closed cervical
reduction. like. an hour ago.

367
00:14:10.725 --> 00:14:12.977
- Oh. I heard.
That must have been so intense.

368
00:14:14.687 --> 00:14:16.814
- My hands are still shaking.

369
00:14:16.856 --> 00:14:18.858
- Hey. um. do you think
you could teach me

370
00:14:18.900 --> 00:14:20.985
how to do that sometime?

371
00:14:21.069 --> 00:14:22.445
- Uh. yeah.

372
00:14:22.528 --> 00:14:23.654
- Yeah?
- Yeah. sure. I mean.

373
00:14:23.738 --> 00:14:25.198
I hope you never
have to use it.

374
00:14:25.281 --> 00:14:27.200
I could have paralyzed
that guy.

375
00:14:27.241 --> 00:14:29.869
- Yeah. but you didn't.

376
00:14:29.952 --> 00:14:33.206
- No. I didn't.

377
00:14:33.247 --> 00:14:35.625
Thank you...

378
00:14:35.708 --> 00:14:37.710
by the way. for...

379
00:14:37.794 --> 00:14:40.463
talking me down earlier.

380
00:14:40.546 --> 00:14:42.423
I'm sorry I snapped.

381
00:14:43.925 --> 00:14:45.259
- It's OK.

382
00:14:53.434 --> 00:14:56.020
- Dr. Mohan. you ever heard
of kinship fostering?

383
00:14:56.104 --> 00:14:57.730
It's where a nurse
or doctor can

384
00:14:57.814 --> 00:14:59.232
become an emergency foster--
- Oh. no.

385
00:14:59.315 --> 00:15:00.733
I don't need any kids.

386
00:15:00.817 --> 00:15:02.902
I need to find a job first.

387
00:15:02.985 --> 00:15:05.363
Candice O'Grady is
an 82-year-old female

388
00:15:05.446 --> 00:15:07.907
brought in by her son
for intractable vomiting.

389
00:15:07.949 --> 00:15:10.910
No fever. no chills.
no abdominal pain. no rash.

390
00:15:11.994 --> 00:15:13.913
- Beep.

391
00:15:13.996 --> 00:15:17.333
- Oh. I've already got one
I can barely keep up with.

392
00:15:17.417 --> 00:15:19.252
- What about Sleeping Beauty
over here?

393
00:15:19.293 --> 00:15:21.254
- She's already babysitting
Whitaker.

394
00:15:21.337 --> 00:15:23.339
- Well. if you know anyone
who'd like to help us out

395
00:15:23.423 --> 00:15:25.258
with Baby Jane Doe.
have them call the main desk.

396
00:15:25.341 --> 00:15:26.926
- Sure thing.

397
00:15:26.968 --> 00:15:30.138
- I'd take her myself.
but Benji'd kill me.

398
00:15:31.514 --> 00:15:33.266
- BP's 164/114.

399
00:15:33.307 --> 00:15:34.600
- Another 40 of labetalol.

400
00:15:34.684 --> 00:15:35.768
- Mag bolus is in.

401
00:15:35.810 --> 00:15:37.437
Now infusing 2 grams an hour.

402
00:15:37.478 --> 00:15:38.688
- Labs are coming back.

403
00:15:38.771 --> 00:15:40.940
Hemoglobin 7.5. platelets 40.

404
00:15:41.023 --> 00:15:42.942
LFTs are sky high.

405
00:15:43.025 --> 00:15:44.735
- HELLP syndrome.
- Hemolytic anemia.

406
00:15:44.819 --> 00:15:47.113
elevated liver enzymes.
and low platelets.

407
00:15:47.155 --> 00:15:48.448
- They're cleaning a room.

408
00:15:48.531 --> 00:15:50.408
We can bring her up
in ten minutes.

409
00:15:50.491 --> 00:15:51.701
- How you doing. Judith?

410
00:15:53.703 --> 00:15:56.164
- I--I--

411
00:15:56.247 --> 00:15:57.832
[machine beeping]
- Oh. she's seizing.

412
00:15:57.915 --> 00:15:59.500
- Oh. shit.

413
00:15:59.584 --> 00:16:02.086
10 of IV diazepam.
Have another 10 ready.

414
00:16:02.170 --> 00:16:04.088
- With all the movement.
we can't get a fetal heartbeat.

415
00:16:04.130 --> 00:16:06.340
- Putting on 15 liters by mask.
Should we intubate?

416
00:16:06.424 --> 00:16:08.342
- Hold intubation.
Let's try to break this.

417
00:16:08.426 --> 00:16:10.303
We don't want to mask seizures
with paralysis

418
00:16:10.344 --> 00:16:11.846
unless we have to.

419
00:16:11.929 --> 00:16:13.431
OK. um...

420
00:16:13.514 --> 00:16:15.892
[rapid beeping]

421
00:16:15.975 --> 00:16:17.643
Crus. CTG isn't reading.

422
00:16:17.727 --> 00:16:19.145
Check with ultrasound.
- On it.

423
00:16:19.187 --> 00:16:20.730
- Nazely. what's the diagnosis?

424
00:16:20.813 --> 00:16:23.858
- Um. with the seizure.
now it's eclampsia.

425
00:16:25.026 --> 00:16:26.986
- Fetal heart rate is about 90.
- Way too low.

426
00:16:27.069 --> 00:16:28.279
- Mom's sats are going down.

427
00:16:28.362 --> 00:16:29.739
- Time to tube her?

428
00:16:29.822 --> 00:16:31.407
- Set up for it. but wait.

429
00:16:31.491 --> 00:16:32.742
Another 10 of diazepam.

430
00:16:32.825 --> 00:16:35.286
Push 4 grams of Keppra.

431
00:16:36.496 --> 00:16:37.997
[baby fussing]

432
00:16:38.039 --> 00:16:39.499
- History of hypertension

433
00:16:39.540 --> 00:16:40.833
presents to the emergency
department

434
00:16:40.875 --> 00:16:43.169
with a chief complaint
of dizziness

435
00:16:43.211 --> 00:16:45.338
after inadvertently
ingesting 80 milligrams--

436
00:16:45.421 --> 00:16:46.672
- Hey. how are you guys
making out?

437
00:16:46.714 --> 00:16:47.715
- Yeah. we're getting there.

438
00:16:47.798 --> 00:16:49.509
- Have you seen Dr. Al-Hashimi?

439
00:16:49.550 --> 00:16:51.385
- No.
- Can I talk to you for a sec?

440
00:16:56.933 --> 00:16:58.184
So I just wanted
to let you know that I've been

441
00:16:58.267 --> 00:16:59.477
checking out some
of your online posts--

442
00:16:59.560 --> 00:17:00.686
- Look. I was just
trying to help

443
00:17:00.728 --> 00:17:02.230
get some health messages
out there.

444
00:17:02.313 --> 00:17:03.814
especially for young people.
- I think they're great.

445
00:17:03.898 --> 00:17:05.816
Really good.

446
00:17:05.900 --> 00:17:07.818
- You do?
- Yeah.

447
00:17:07.902 --> 00:17:10.029
Yeah. um. keep it up.

448
00:17:10.112 --> 00:17:11.489
- OK.

449
00:17:11.572 --> 00:17:13.824
- As long as you follow
the HIPAA laws.

450
00:17:13.908 --> 00:17:15.201
- I do.

451
00:17:15.284 --> 00:17:16.786
- And wait until
you're done charting.

452
00:17:16.869 --> 00:17:18.496
- [scoffs] Sure.

453
00:17:20.706 --> 00:17:24.961
Actually. Dr. Robby--sorry.
um. can I ask you a question?

454
00:17:25.044 --> 00:17:26.170
- Shoot.

455
00:17:26.254 --> 00:17:27.672
- Um. I--I may be

456
00:17:27.713 --> 00:17:30.508
considering
emergency psychiatry.

457
00:17:31.759 --> 00:17:33.886
- Very cool.

458
00:17:33.970 --> 00:17:35.763
- Think I could do it?

459
00:17:37.932 --> 00:17:39.392
- I think that you could do

460
00:17:39.433 --> 00:17:42.019
anything that you put
your mind to. Victoria.

461
00:17:46.107 --> 00:17:47.483
- OK.

462
00:17:47.567 --> 00:17:49.193
- Pulse ox is 88.

463
00:17:49.277 --> 00:17:50.403
[rapid beeping]

464
00:17:50.444 --> 00:17:52.405
- Dr. Abbot?

465
00:17:52.488 --> 00:17:54.574
Intubate?
- Let's do it.

466
00:17:54.657 --> 00:17:57.910
Nazely. what do you suggest
for rapid sequence induction?

467
00:17:57.994 --> 00:17:59.120
- Etomidate and roc.

468
00:17:59.203 --> 00:18:00.288
- Mm. not quite.

469
00:18:00.371 --> 00:18:01.414
120 of propofol.

470
00:18:01.497 --> 00:18:02.415
60 of succinylcholine.

471
00:18:02.498 --> 00:18:03.916
Why is that. Crus?

472
00:18:03.958 --> 00:18:05.585
- Propofol
for the anti-seizure effect.

473
00:18:05.668 --> 00:18:07.253
sux to avoid
prolonged paralysis

474
00:18:07.295 --> 00:18:09.297
so we can check her neuro exam.
- Exactly.

475
00:18:09.380 --> 00:18:10.631
- Pushing the propofol.

476
00:18:10.715 --> 00:18:12.133
- Once she's flat
for intubation.

477
00:18:12.216 --> 00:18:13.759
we need to displace
the uterus to the left.

478
00:18:13.801 --> 00:18:15.386
- Nazely. that's you.
Big hug. both arms.

479
00:18:15.428 --> 00:18:17.722
Get the baby off the vena cava.
- Sux is on board.

480
00:18:17.763 --> 00:18:20.433
- But after she's paralyzed.
the seizing stops. right?

481
00:18:20.516 --> 00:18:21.934
- It might look like that.

482
00:18:22.018 --> 00:18:24.020
but an ongoing seizure
will still fry the brain.

483
00:18:24.103 --> 00:18:25.855
We monitor with EEG.

484
00:18:25.938 --> 00:18:27.815
- Is there time for that?
- Wait and see.

485
00:18:28.941 --> 00:18:30.109
- Paralytics kicked in.

486
00:18:30.192 --> 00:18:31.736
- Let's go.
Roll her to her back.

487
00:18:32.778 --> 00:18:34.405
- Intubate. then EEG

488
00:18:34.488 --> 00:18:36.949
to see if her brain is
still seizing.

489
00:18:36.991 --> 00:18:38.451
I need first pass success.

490
00:18:38.534 --> 00:18:39.702
- You and me both.

491
00:18:39.785 --> 00:18:42.830
[machinery beeping]

492
00:18:46.000 --> 00:18:47.460
[indistinct chatter]

493
00:18:47.501 --> 00:18:49.962
- [sighs]
Have you seen Dr. Al-Hashimi?

494
00:18:50.046 --> 00:18:51.172
- No.

495
00:18:51.255 --> 00:18:53.591
- Have you seen Dr. Al-Hashimi?

496
00:18:53.674 --> 00:18:55.343
Al-Hashimi?

497
00:18:55.426 --> 00:18:57.970
- With how this day's going.
she probably quit.

498
00:18:58.012 --> 00:19:01.182
- Last I saw her. she was
in Peds with Baby Jane Doe.

499
00:19:01.265 --> 00:19:03.643
- Nope. I was just in there.

500
00:19:03.684 --> 00:19:04.644
- Want me to page her?

501
00:19:04.685 --> 00:19:06.437
- Uh. no. that's OK.

502
00:19:06.520 --> 00:19:07.813
I will find her.

503
00:19:12.401 --> 00:19:13.653
Hello.

504
00:19:16.447 --> 00:19:18.824
Hey. how did our people do
at the deposition?

505
00:19:18.866 --> 00:19:21.327
- Oh. well.
Dr. Ellis is a pit bull.

506
00:19:21.410 --> 00:19:23.454
Dr. King is a petunia.

507
00:19:23.537 --> 00:19:24.789
They were pretty brutal
with her.

508
00:19:24.872 --> 00:19:26.666
- She's sensitive.
- Very.

509
00:19:26.707 --> 00:19:28.250
And I'm afraid it isn't over.

510
00:19:28.334 --> 00:19:29.418
They want to call her back.

511
00:19:29.502 --> 00:19:31.253
- Oh. that's unfortunate.

512
00:19:31.337 --> 00:19:32.505
Maybe I should go with you

513
00:19:32.546 --> 00:19:34.173
to break that news to her.
actually.

514
00:19:34.215 --> 00:19:36.008
- Misery loves company.
- Um. hey. while I have you.

515
00:19:36.050 --> 00:19:38.761
can I pose a hypothetical
to you?

516
00:19:38.844 --> 00:19:40.763
If a doctor suspects
another physician

517
00:19:40.846 --> 00:19:43.015
of having a medical condition
that could negatively

518
00:19:43.099 --> 00:19:45.184
affect the way they
would treat a patient.

519
00:19:45.226 --> 00:19:46.852
where would
disclosing that fall

520
00:19:46.936 --> 00:19:48.938
on the HIPAA violation scale?

521
00:19:49.939 --> 00:19:51.941
- First. do no harm.

522
00:19:54.402 --> 00:19:56.821
Dr. King. do you have a second?

523
00:19:59.407 --> 00:20:02.201
- Mm...

524
00:20:03.994 --> 00:20:05.996
- Good lung sliding
bilaterally.

525
00:20:06.080 --> 00:20:08.082
- Fetal heart rate
borderline at 98.

526
00:20:09.583 --> 00:20:11.711
- Roll her to the left again.
That can help.

527
00:20:11.752 --> 00:20:14.880
- One. two. three.
- [grunts]

528
00:20:14.922 --> 00:20:18.342
OK. all set here.

529
00:20:18.426 --> 00:20:19.844
- EEG monitor's good to go.

530
00:20:19.927 --> 00:20:21.595
- That was fast.

531
00:20:21.679 --> 00:20:23.055
- Still seizing
while paralyzed.

532
00:20:23.139 --> 00:20:25.641
It's nonconvulsive status.

533
00:20:25.725 --> 00:20:27.017
- What's she had so far?

534
00:20:27.101 --> 00:20:28.686
- 30 of diazepam.
a full load of mag.

535
00:20:28.769 --> 00:20:29.895
Keppra. and propofol.

536
00:20:29.937 --> 00:20:31.230
- Damn. What's your next step?

537
00:20:31.313 --> 00:20:32.481
- Any ideas?

538
00:20:32.565 --> 00:20:34.734
Hmm? Nazely?

539
00:20:34.775 --> 00:20:36.652
- Dilantin? Valproate?

540
00:20:36.736 --> 00:20:37.987
- Mm. infusion is too long.

541
00:20:38.070 --> 00:20:39.530
So is onset of action.

542
00:20:39.613 --> 00:20:40.990
Push 100 of ketamine.

543
00:20:41.073 --> 00:20:43.242
That's had results
with refractory status.

544
00:20:43.284 --> 00:20:45.536
- She also has HELLP syndrome--
hemoglobin only 7.

545
00:20:45.578 --> 00:20:48.414
platelets down to 30.
- Two units whole blood?

546
00:20:48.497 --> 00:20:50.875
- O-neg is going up on
the rapid infuser as we speak.

547
00:20:50.958 --> 00:20:52.918
- Uh. put the AP pads on.
just in case.

548
00:20:53.002 --> 00:20:55.755
- And 10 of Decadron IV push
for the inflammatory storm.

549
00:20:55.796 --> 00:20:57.882
- Fetal heart rate up to 104.
- Hmm.

550
00:20:57.965 --> 00:20:59.216
- Little better.
- Yeah.

551
00:20:59.300 --> 00:21:01.594
She should be upstairs with OB.

552
00:21:01.635 --> 00:21:05.306
- She will be
after we break this seizure.

553
00:21:05.389 --> 00:21:08.559
- There was a delay
in history-taking

554
00:21:08.601 --> 00:21:11.645
due to a malfunctioning
VRI interpretation device.

555
00:21:11.729 --> 00:21:14.273
During this time.
there was a normal CBC

556
00:21:14.315 --> 00:21:15.941
and comprehensive
metabolic panel

557
00:21:15.983 --> 00:21:17.693
that came back from the lab.

558
00:21:19.153 --> 00:21:20.988
What's wrong with you.
Malfeasance?

559
00:21:21.071 --> 00:21:23.991
- I have to do
another deposition.

560
00:21:24.074 --> 00:21:25.951
- Oh. that sucks.

561
00:21:26.035 --> 00:21:27.995
You must have really messed up.
[chuckles]

562
00:21:29.038 --> 00:21:30.706
Dude. I'm joking.

563
00:21:30.790 --> 00:21:31.791
You gotta lighten up.

564
00:21:31.832 --> 00:21:33.501
It's all just bullshit.

565
00:21:35.002 --> 00:21:37.379
[sighs] God. you know what?
Fuck all this.

566
00:21:37.463 --> 00:21:38.839
Do you want to go get a drink?

567
00:21:39.965 --> 00:21:40.925
- Me?

568
00:21:41.008 --> 00:21:42.593
- Yes. you.

569
00:21:42.676 --> 00:21:44.929
You--you do go out. don't you?

570
00:21:45.012 --> 00:21:47.139
- Well. I'm usually with Becca.

571
00:21:47.181 --> 00:21:48.432
- Well. bring her along.

572
00:21:48.516 --> 00:21:49.767
Can she drive?

573
00:21:49.850 --> 00:21:52.102
- No. and she's
with her boyfriend.

574
00:21:53.062 --> 00:21:54.522
- OK. Becca.

575
00:21:56.190 --> 00:21:58.150
So it's just you and me.

576
00:22:00.277 --> 00:22:02.655
Do you like karaoke?

577
00:22:02.696 --> 00:22:04.490
- You do karaoke?

578
00:22:04.573 --> 00:22:08.869
- Well. what I do is more like
primal scream therapy.

579
00:22:08.953 --> 00:22:10.621
There's nothing like
getting wasted

580
00:22:10.704 --> 00:22:12.122
and just absolutely wailing

581
00:22:12.206 --> 00:22:14.875
to shake off a shit show
like today.

582
00:22:14.959 --> 00:22:16.836
- I could use a fun night.

583
00:22:18.212 --> 00:22:20.005
- You and me both. sister.

584
00:22:20.089 --> 00:22:21.799
- There's been no improvement.

585
00:22:21.882 --> 00:22:23.342
Still seizing on the EEG.

586
00:22:23.425 --> 00:22:25.052
Neurology has been called.
- OK. Got it.

587
00:22:25.135 --> 00:22:27.012
OB says send her up.
They have an OR ready.

588
00:22:27.096 --> 00:22:28.514
- About time.

589
00:22:28.556 --> 00:22:30.182
- Baby's been bradying down
a bit more.

590
00:22:30.266 --> 00:22:31.767
- This one looks like
it took a turn for the worse.

591
00:22:31.851 --> 00:22:33.602
- Eclampsia.
refractory seizures.

592
00:22:33.686 --> 00:22:35.855
HELLP syndrome with anemia
and thrombocytopenia.

593
00:22:35.938 --> 00:22:37.314
- Yeah.
about as bad as it gets.

594
00:22:37.398 --> 00:22:39.817
[alarm blaring]
- V-fib!

595
00:22:39.900 --> 00:22:41.861
- Chest compressions. Nazely.

596
00:22:41.902 --> 00:22:44.613
Charge to 200.

597
00:22:44.697 --> 00:22:46.031
- Prep the belly.

598
00:22:46.115 --> 00:22:47.366
Get a baby warmer.

599
00:22:47.449 --> 00:22:49.034
Call the NICU. Start a timer.

600
00:22:49.118 --> 00:22:50.870
- Charged.

601
00:22:50.953 --> 00:22:52.162
Clear.

602
00:22:52.246 --> 00:22:53.998
<i>[tense music]</i>

603
00:22:54.081 --> 00:22:55.332
- Continue compressions.

604
00:22:55.416 --> 00:22:57.710
We'll check a rhythm
in a minute.

605
00:22:57.793 --> 00:22:59.044
- Gown up.

606
00:22:59.086 --> 00:23:00.379
Robby. it's you and me.

607
00:23:00.421 --> 00:23:02.381
- Nazely.
what's the four-minute rule?

608
00:23:02.423 --> 00:23:04.592
- Uh. not sure.

609
00:23:04.675 --> 00:23:06.385
- Pregnant patient
with a viable fetus.

610
00:23:06.468 --> 00:23:08.053
you have four minutes
after cardiac arrest

611
00:23:08.095 --> 00:23:10.347
to save the baby.
- And the mom.

612
00:23:10.389 --> 00:23:12.600
We don't call it a postmortem
C-section anymore.

613
00:23:12.683 --> 00:23:13.893
It's a resuscitative
hysterotomy

614
00:23:13.934 --> 00:23:15.394
to try to save them both.

615
00:23:15.436 --> 00:23:16.687
- But she doesn't want
any medical intervention.

616
00:23:16.770 --> 00:23:18.063
- That doesn't matter.

617
00:23:18.147 --> 00:23:19.565
Mom and baby are both dead
if we do nothing.

618
00:23:19.648 --> 00:23:21.400
OK. charge to 200.

619
00:23:21.442 --> 00:23:23.485
One more rhythm check and then
Abbot and I are gonna cut.

620
00:23:24.778 --> 00:23:27.281
Ellis. you and Crus
on Mom resuscitation.

621
00:23:27.364 --> 00:23:28.741
Shen. you and Nazely
take the baby.

622
00:23:28.824 --> 00:23:30.242
OK. hold compressions.

623
00:23:30.326 --> 00:23:31.911
<i>♪ ♪</i>

624
00:23:31.994 --> 00:23:33.537
- Still V-fib.

625
00:23:33.621 --> 00:23:34.705
- Clear.

626
00:23:34.788 --> 00:23:36.582
[thud]
- No change.

627
00:23:36.624 --> 00:23:38.584
Resume compression. amp of epi.
- OK. showtime.

628
00:23:38.667 --> 00:23:40.252
- We need to get this baby out
right now.

629
00:23:40.336 --> 00:23:41.462
- OK. take a break.

630
00:23:44.006 --> 00:23:47.426
- OK. 10 blade. Good.

631
00:23:47.509 --> 00:23:49.678
First incision is
from the xiphoid

632
00:23:49.762 --> 00:23:51.430
to the pubic symphysis

633
00:23:51.472 --> 00:23:54.391
through the skin
to the linea alba.

634
00:23:54.475 --> 00:23:56.560
- Units three and four
on the infuser.

635
00:23:56.602 --> 00:23:59.396
- Second incision goes
through the peritoneum.

636
00:23:59.480 --> 00:24:01.190
exposing the uterus.

637
00:24:01.273 --> 00:24:02.900
- Where do you need me?

638
00:24:02.983 --> 00:24:05.110
- You're with the baby.
Nazely's got the bag mask.

639
00:24:05.194 --> 00:24:07.321
You're on suction.
Stand by for intubation.

640
00:24:07.404 --> 00:24:08.822
- Bladder retractors.

641
00:24:08.906 --> 00:24:10.491
- Neonatal monitor
and pulse ox ready to go.

642
00:24:10.574 --> 00:24:12.952
- Ellis. gentle traction.

643
00:24:12.993 --> 00:24:14.995
OK. making a small
vertical incision

644
00:24:15.079 --> 00:24:18.624
through the lower uterus
so as not to cut the baby.

645
00:24:18.707 --> 00:24:20.459
- Mm-hmm.

646
00:24:20.501 --> 00:24:21.961
- Got it?
- Yep. I got it.

647
00:24:22.044 --> 00:24:23.420
- OK.
- OK.

648
00:24:23.504 --> 00:24:26.590
Using scissors
to extend superiorly.

649
00:24:26.632 --> 00:24:28.008
<i>♪ ♪</i>

650
00:24:28.092 --> 00:24:30.135
- Ellis. hand retract
the uterus with me.

651
00:24:30.177 --> 00:24:32.012
- Amniotic fluid looks good.

652
00:24:32.096 --> 00:24:33.639
<i>♪ ♪</i>

653
00:24:33.722 --> 00:24:35.391
- Give me some fundal pressure.

654
00:24:35.474 --> 00:24:36.809
- Breech position.

655
00:24:36.892 --> 00:24:39.228
<i>♪ ♪</i>

656
00:24:39.311 --> 00:24:42.398
- OK. baby's out.

657
00:24:42.481 --> 00:24:44.233
It's a girl.
- All right.

658
00:24:44.316 --> 00:24:45.901
<i>♪ ♪</i>

659
00:24:45.985 --> 00:24:48.904
Milking the cord.

660
00:24:48.988 --> 00:24:51.407
- Clamping.

661
00:24:51.490 --> 00:24:53.409
- Cutting.

662
00:24:53.492 --> 00:24:54.994
- OK. blue and flaccid.
Coming to you. Shen.

663
00:24:55.077 --> 00:24:56.161
You ready?
- Yeah. you got her.

664
00:24:56.203 --> 00:24:58.163
- I got it. yep.

665
00:24:58.247 --> 00:24:59.581
OK.

666
00:24:59.665 --> 00:25:03.168
[rapid beeping]

667
00:25:03.252 --> 00:25:05.629
Poor tone. no movement.

668
00:25:05.713 --> 00:25:08.298
- Keep the blow-by closer.

669
00:25:08.382 --> 00:25:09.675
- She's really blue.

670
00:25:09.758 --> 00:25:12.511
- Some blue is normal.
but not this much.

671
00:25:12.594 --> 00:25:14.471
- Do we need to intubate?
- Not yet. no.

672
00:25:14.555 --> 00:25:17.182
They usually pink up
with stimulation and blow-by.

673
00:25:17.266 --> 00:25:19.018
- OK. removing the placenta.

674
00:25:19.059 --> 00:25:21.353
- Sweeping to the left.
trying to get it in one piece.

675
00:25:21.437 --> 00:25:23.188
<i>♪ ♪</i>

676
00:25:23.272 --> 00:25:24.523
- Looks intact.
- Yeah.

677
00:25:24.565 --> 00:25:26.650
- Nicely done.

678
00:25:26.734 --> 00:25:28.652
- 10 of IV Pitocin
to contract the uterus.

679
00:25:28.736 --> 00:25:30.863
- And lots of massage.

680
00:25:30.904 --> 00:25:32.489
- Heart rate 76.

681
00:25:32.573 --> 00:25:34.074
- Less than 100 means
we need to bag.

682
00:25:34.158 --> 00:25:35.284
Suction first.

683
00:25:35.367 --> 00:25:36.452
- OK.

684
00:25:36.535 --> 00:25:38.370
<i>♪ ♪</i>

685
00:25:38.454 --> 00:25:39.830
- Hey. Jord. charge to 200.

686
00:25:39.913 --> 00:25:42.708
Stand by for the next
rhythm check.

687
00:25:42.750 --> 00:25:44.376
- She grimaced. Good sign.

688
00:25:44.460 --> 00:25:45.461
- Bagging.

689
00:25:45.544 --> 00:25:47.463
- Pulse ox 45%.

690
00:25:47.546 --> 00:25:49.048
- Oh. I've never seen it
that low.

691
00:25:49.131 --> 00:25:50.883
- It's not as bad as it sounds.

692
00:25:50.924 --> 00:25:52.885
I'm more worried
about the heart rate.

693
00:25:52.968 --> 00:25:55.054
McKay. get ready with an IO
in case we need epi.

694
00:25:55.137 --> 00:25:56.513
- OK.

695
00:25:56.597 --> 00:25:58.348
[whirring]

696
00:25:58.432 --> 00:26:00.851
- Rhythm check.
Hold compressions.

697
00:26:00.934 --> 00:26:01.894
- Still V-fib.

698
00:26:01.977 --> 00:26:03.395
OK. shock it.
- Clear.

699
00:26:03.479 --> 00:26:04.396
[thud]

700
00:26:04.480 --> 00:26:05.898
Resume compressions.

701
00:26:05.981 --> 00:26:07.399
- Shen. how's she doing
over there?

702
00:26:07.483 --> 00:26:08.734
- Heart rate's up to 104.

703
00:26:08.776 --> 00:26:09.943
- Uh. at one minute.

704
00:26:10.027 --> 00:26:12.279
she's 0 for color.
2 for heart rate.

705
00:26:12.362 --> 00:26:13.614
1 for reflex. tone. breathing.

706
00:26:13.697 --> 00:26:15.240
APGAR of 5.

707
00:26:15.324 --> 00:26:17.201
- 5 out of 10. Not great.

708
00:26:17.284 --> 00:26:18.911
- Pulse ox 58%.

709
00:26:18.952 --> 00:26:20.788
- Intubation?
- Uh. not yet.

710
00:26:20.871 --> 00:26:22.915
O2 sat in the 60s is normal
at one minute.

711
00:26:22.956 --> 00:26:25.751
- Her heart rate and pulse ox
are trending higher.

712
00:26:25.834 --> 00:26:27.211
- Let's keep doing
what we're doing.

713
00:26:27.294 --> 00:26:28.754
A little tincture of time.

714
00:26:28.796 --> 00:26:30.422
- Hold compressions.

715
00:26:30.464 --> 00:26:32.466
- Looks like sinus.

716
00:26:32.549 --> 00:26:34.134
- Can't feel a carotid.

717
00:26:34.218 --> 00:26:35.552
- No.

718
00:26:35.636 --> 00:26:37.554
- Heart's barely pumping.
It's PEA.

719
00:26:37.638 --> 00:26:38.847
- Back on compressions.

720
00:26:38.931 --> 00:26:40.349
- Transfuse two more units.

721
00:26:40.432 --> 00:26:41.767
She needs more red cells
and platelets.

722
00:26:41.809 --> 00:26:43.435
- Ongoing blood loss
from the uterus.

723
00:26:43.519 --> 00:26:45.020
Give me all the lap pads
we got. please.

724
00:26:45.104 --> 00:26:48.023
[rapid beeping]

725
00:26:48.107 --> 00:26:52.444
<i>♪ ♪</i>

726
00:26:52.528 --> 00:26:53.779
- Yeah.

727
00:26:53.862 --> 00:26:54.905
OK. yeah. thanks.

728
00:26:54.988 --> 00:26:56.365
I appreciate it. honey.

729
00:26:56.448 --> 00:26:58.283
Oh. gotta go.

730
00:26:58.325 --> 00:26:59.618
Whoa. whoa. whoa!

731
00:26:59.660 --> 00:27:00.619
Hold up.

732
00:27:00.661 --> 00:27:02.121
- Is there a problem here?

733
00:27:02.162 --> 00:27:04.206
- Yeah. you two aren't leaving
empty-handed.

734
00:27:04.289 --> 00:27:05.332
- What?

735
00:27:06.500 --> 00:27:08.043
- One of you follow me.

736
00:27:09.711 --> 00:27:11.463
Rape kits are supposed
to be picked up

737
00:27:11.547 --> 00:27:14.424
within 72 hours
of collecting 'em.

738
00:27:14.508 --> 00:27:17.136
This one's been here
for over two weeks.

739
00:27:17.219 --> 00:27:18.846
- That's not on us.

740
00:27:18.929 --> 00:27:20.472
- Well. it's on somebody.

741
00:27:20.514 --> 00:27:21.974
It's not bad enough
these poor women

742
00:27:22.015 --> 00:27:23.517
go through an assault.
plus the indignity

743
00:27:23.600 --> 00:27:25.185
of the whole
collection process.

744
00:27:25.269 --> 00:27:26.979
but nobody from
the police department

745
00:27:27.020 --> 00:27:29.523
even has the human decency
to come get these things?

746
00:27:29.606 --> 00:27:30.649
Like nobody there
gives a flying fuck?

747
00:27:30.732 --> 00:27:32.276
- OK. we got it.

748
00:27:32.359 --> 00:27:34.194
We'll see that these get
put into evidence properly.

749
00:27:34.278 --> 00:27:35.487
- Thank you.

750
00:27:37.614 --> 00:27:38.866
How hard was that?

751
00:27:41.410 --> 00:27:42.619
[rapid beeping]

752
00:27:42.703 --> 00:27:43.829
- Units five and six are in.

753
00:27:43.871 --> 00:27:45.247
- Down to a slow ooze here.

754
00:27:45.330 --> 00:27:46.665
- Hold compressions.

755
00:27:46.707 --> 00:27:50.169
[machinery beeping]

756
00:27:50.252 --> 00:27:52.254
- Looks like sinus.

757
00:27:52.337 --> 00:27:53.672
And I got a weak carotid.
- OK.

758
00:27:53.714 --> 00:27:55.174
Cycle the BP.

759
00:27:55.215 --> 00:27:57.259
- Better filling.
better squeeze.

760
00:27:57.342 --> 00:27:58.844
- No seizure activity
on the EEG.

761
00:27:58.927 --> 00:28:00.345
- That's progress.
That's progress.

762
00:28:00.429 --> 00:28:01.430
- We're at five minutes.

763
00:28:01.513 --> 00:28:03.348
- Uh. heart rate is 132.

764
00:28:03.432 --> 00:28:05.017
Uh. pulse ox 79%.

765
00:28:05.100 --> 00:28:06.935
Nazely. the APGAR?

766
00:28:07.019 --> 00:28:08.520
- Um...

767
00:28:08.562 --> 00:28:10.647
1 off for color.
1 off for tone.

768
00:28:10.731 --> 00:28:13.192
1 off for respiration
with hypoxia. total of 7.

769
00:28:13.275 --> 00:28:14.568
- Respiration score is
for observed breathing.

770
00:28:14.651 --> 00:28:16.028
not pulse ox.

771
00:28:16.069 --> 00:28:17.529
- Sat of 80 is normal
at five minutes.

772
00:28:17.613 --> 00:28:19.031
With no crying.
she still gets 1 off.

773
00:28:19.072 --> 00:28:20.115
- Yeah.

774
00:28:22.492 --> 00:28:23.911
[baby crying]
- Ah!

775
00:28:23.994 --> 00:28:25.871
She just scored
the winning point!

776
00:28:25.954 --> 00:28:28.290
APGAR of 8 is pretty normal.

777
00:28:31.585 --> 00:28:33.837
- Holy shit. What did I miss?

778
00:28:33.921 --> 00:28:36.548
- Eclampsia with status.
HELLP syndrome.

779
00:28:36.632 --> 00:28:39.718
cardiac arrest.
resuscitative hysterotomy.

780
00:28:39.801 --> 00:28:42.054
- I was in the OR
with a septic twin C-section.

781
00:28:42.137 --> 00:28:43.347
Got your text 12 minutes ago.

782
00:28:43.430 --> 00:28:44.890
- Shit happens fast down here.

783
00:28:44.932 --> 00:28:47.392
- Resuscitative hysterotomy
in 36 seconds.

784
00:28:47.476 --> 00:28:49.728
- Impressive.
- BP's 102/64.

785
00:28:49.770 --> 00:28:50.896
Hemoglobin is up to 9.

786
00:28:50.979 --> 00:28:52.981
- That'll do.

787
00:28:53.065 --> 00:28:54.399
- NICU's sending a team down.

788
00:28:54.441 --> 00:28:56.735
- We can take Mom.
You guys are rock stars.

789
00:28:56.777 --> 00:28:59.279
- We like to be referred to
as crawlers of the night.

790
00:29:00.906 --> 00:29:02.407
- [sighs]

791
00:29:02.449 --> 00:29:03.742
If you're not careful.

792
00:29:03.825 --> 00:29:05.327
you're gonna get stuck
here all night.

793
00:29:05.410 --> 00:29:07.829
- Nah. Henny said she'd
be here in 30 minutes.

794
00:29:07.913 --> 00:29:10.415
How's Mom and baby?
- Whew.

795
00:29:10.457 --> 00:29:12.376
They're both gonna go upstairs.

796
00:29:12.459 --> 00:29:14.544
- Good. You leaving now?

797
00:29:14.628 --> 00:29:16.213
- Yeah. pretty soon.

798
00:29:16.296 --> 00:29:19.299
I gotta find Whitaker.
I gotta find Al-Hashimi.

799
00:29:19.383 --> 00:29:21.593
and I gotta find Langdon
before I leave.

800
00:29:21.635 --> 00:29:24.137
- You missed Langdon.
He just checked out.

801
00:29:26.556 --> 00:29:28.600
- [sighs] Shit.

802
00:29:52.040 --> 00:29:53.417
- Can I help you?

803
00:29:53.458 --> 00:29:56.962
- Uh. yeah. I'm Dr. Langdon
from the ED.

804
00:29:57.004 --> 00:29:59.881
I was just. uh.
checking in on the status

805
00:29:59.965 --> 00:30:02.551
of someone we sent up here
earlier.

806
00:30:02.634 --> 00:30:05.137
Patient's name is. uh. Cohen.

807
00:30:05.220 --> 00:30:06.430
- Let me check.

808
00:30:06.513 --> 00:30:07.723
What was she up here for?

809
00:30:07.806 --> 00:30:09.558
- Uh. clean out
a nasty neck fash.

810
00:30:09.641 --> 00:30:12.227
[keys clacking]

811
00:30:12.311 --> 00:30:13.895
- Oh. yeah. she's good.

812
00:30:13.979 --> 00:30:16.982
She's in 4202.
recovering nicely.

813
00:30:17.065 --> 00:30:19.609
- Great. great.

814
00:30:19.651 --> 00:30:22.487
I mean. she was--she was
in not-great shape earlier.

815
00:30:22.571 --> 00:30:24.656
- It was a good catch.

816
00:30:24.698 --> 00:30:28.660
Saved her life. even if
we couldn't save her leg.

817
00:30:28.702 --> 00:30:31.621
- Uh. was it below the knee?

818
00:30:31.705 --> 00:30:33.540
- Unfortunately. it was above.

819
00:30:50.432 --> 00:30:53.518
- My cell phone
and the building manager's.

820
00:30:53.560 --> 00:30:55.437
He can help if there's
any emergencies.

821
00:30:55.520 --> 00:30:57.522
- Yeah.
what kind of emergencies?

822
00:30:57.606 --> 00:30:58.940
- Whatever.

823
00:30:59.024 --> 00:30:59.941
And follow up with Duke

824
00:31:00.025 --> 00:31:00.942
in a couple days. yeah?

825
00:31:01.026 --> 00:31:01.985
- Yeah.

826
00:31:02.069 --> 00:31:04.363
You. um--you sure about this?

827
00:31:04.446 --> 00:31:06.198
- I trust you. Whitaker.

828
00:31:06.281 --> 00:31:07.991
- Great.

829
00:31:08.075 --> 00:31:09.451
- Any questions?

830
00:31:09.534 --> 00:31:12.537
- Uh. when are you back.
exactly?

831
00:31:12.579 --> 00:31:13.997
- You know. I'll text you.

832
00:31:14.081 --> 00:31:15.916
I'm trying to keep my dates
kind of fluid.

833
00:31:17.292 --> 00:31:19.378
I think this is your ride.

834
00:31:19.419 --> 00:31:21.380
- Yeah. uh. yes.

835
00:31:21.463 --> 00:31:23.924
I--I promise I'll check in
on your house tomorrow.

836
00:31:24.007 --> 00:31:25.509
- Sounds good.

837
00:31:26.635 --> 00:31:28.261
- Hey.
- Hey.

838
00:31:28.345 --> 00:31:31.390
- OK. Hey. Theo.

839
00:31:31.431 --> 00:31:33.225
You're up late. huh?

840
00:31:33.266 --> 00:31:35.936
What you got there?
[chuckles]

841
00:31:37.479 --> 00:31:39.856
OK.

842
00:31:39.940 --> 00:31:41.525
- He's been fussy all day.

843
00:31:41.608 --> 00:31:43.693
I think he's got
another tooth coming in.

844
00:31:43.777 --> 00:31:45.404
- Aw. right on. big guy.

845
00:31:45.445 --> 00:31:48.782
Are you ready to get funky?

846
00:31:48.865 --> 00:31:50.575
Yeah?
- [chuckles]

847
00:31:50.659 --> 00:31:52.869
<i>- ♪ Ain't we funkin' now ♪</i>

848
00:31:52.911 --> 00:31:54.746
<i>[The Brothers Johnson's
"Ain't We Funkin' Now"]</i>

849
00:31:54.788 --> 00:31:56.706
<i>♪ Ain't we funkin' now ♪</i>

850
00:31:56.790 --> 00:32:02.796
<i>♪ ♪</i>

851
00:32:09.761 --> 00:32:11.096
- Hey.

852
00:32:11.138 --> 00:32:13.140
Any luck picking an elective?

853
00:32:14.599 --> 00:32:17.352
- Don't know. [sighs]

854
00:32:17.436 --> 00:32:19.646
Maybe I will go
into geriatrics.

855
00:32:21.148 --> 00:32:23.108
- It's a smart choice.

856
00:32:26.820 --> 00:32:28.405
I know that life can be
challenging.

857
00:32:28.488 --> 00:32:29.781
especially when
it doesn't work out

858
00:32:29.823 --> 00:32:31.116
the way you expected.

859
00:32:31.158 --> 00:32:32.367
- OK.

860
00:32:37.205 --> 00:32:38.623
- I thought I would be married

861
00:32:38.665 --> 00:32:40.750
with two kids in college
by now.

862
00:32:42.043 --> 00:32:44.754
Maybe have some property
with a pond.

863
00:32:44.838 --> 00:32:46.965
and we could play hockey on it
in the wintertime.

864
00:32:47.048 --> 00:32:49.092
[siren wailing]

865
00:32:49.176 --> 00:32:50.302
And yet look at me now.

866
00:32:50.385 --> 00:32:54.514
No wife. no kids. no pond.

867
00:32:57.976 --> 00:33:00.103
- It's never too late.

868
00:33:00.187 --> 00:33:02.606
- Do you really believe that?

869
00:33:02.689 --> 00:33:03.982
- Yeah.

870
00:33:04.024 --> 00:33:05.650
- Only for me. or for you too?

871
00:33:05.734 --> 00:33:07.319
- OK.
[siren chirps]

872
00:33:07.360 --> 00:33:08.945
I see what you did there.

873
00:33:10.155 --> 00:33:12.824
Was that true. or something
you just said to make a point?

874
00:33:12.866 --> 00:33:14.242
[vehicle door opens]

875
00:33:18.997 --> 00:33:21.750
- Have you worked things out
with your mom?

876
00:33:23.960 --> 00:33:25.545
- We're not talking.

877
00:33:28.798 --> 00:33:33.136
I am sorry that. um.
I let it distract me.

878
00:33:34.638 --> 00:33:36.223
She was treating me
like a child.

879
00:33:36.306 --> 00:33:37.724
and I was letting her.

880
00:33:42.896 --> 00:33:44.397
Have a good trip.

881
00:33:45.565 --> 00:33:46.733
Please be safe.

882
00:33:48.652 --> 00:33:51.029
We need you here.

883
00:33:51.071 --> 00:33:53.240
Even if you can be
a dick sometimes.

884
00:33:56.076 --> 00:33:57.285
Good luck.

885
00:33:58.620 --> 00:33:59.996
- You too.

886
00:34:05.752 --> 00:34:06.711
[loud bang]

887
00:34:06.753 --> 00:34:08.338
[car alarm blaring]

888
00:34:09.089 --> 00:34:11.174
Hey. I didn't think
you were still here.

889
00:34:11.258 --> 00:34:13.677
- I was just talking
to the neurologist on call.

890
00:34:15.095 --> 00:34:16.805
- And?

891
00:34:16.888 --> 00:34:20.141
- We had a nice chat.

892
00:34:20.225 --> 00:34:22.811
She agrees I can work
with double coverage.

893
00:34:22.894 --> 00:34:25.230
- That's not her call to make.

894
00:34:25.272 --> 00:34:26.565
You can't do anything critical

895
00:34:26.648 --> 00:34:28.066
where a five-second lapse
in consciousness

896
00:34:28.149 --> 00:34:29.943
could potentially
kill a patient.

897
00:34:31.778 --> 00:34:32.988
- I agree.

898
00:34:35.115 --> 00:34:36.408
- [sighs]

899
00:34:36.449 --> 00:34:37.701
- But 90% of our patients

900
00:34:37.742 --> 00:34:38.952
don't require
critical procedures.

901
00:34:39.035 --> 00:34:41.121
- And the ones that do?

902
00:34:41.204 --> 00:34:43.540
- Will be handled by
whomever is working with me.

903
00:34:43.623 --> 00:34:45.417
- Unless they're also tied up
with a critical patient.

904
00:34:45.500 --> 00:34:46.793
What if it's a double
or triple trauma?

905
00:34:46.876 --> 00:34:48.795
- Robby. I can handle it.
- No. you can't.

906
00:34:48.878 --> 00:34:50.255
And I can't let you.

907
00:34:50.297 --> 00:34:51.631
- I am fully capable
of handling--

908
00:34:51.715 --> 00:34:53.258
- No. you are not
fully capable.

909
00:34:53.300 --> 00:34:54.759
and you know it.

910
00:34:58.471 --> 00:34:59.889
- What do you want from me?

911
00:34:59.973 --> 00:35:01.016
- I want what's best
for this department--

912
00:35:01.099 --> 00:35:02.434
patients and staff.

913
00:35:02.517 --> 00:35:04.728
Best-case scenario.
you get a handle on this.

914
00:35:04.811 --> 00:35:06.271
you're seizure-free
for six months.

915
00:35:06.354 --> 00:35:07.522
you get your
driver's license back.

916
00:35:07.606 --> 00:35:08.773
you are cleared to work.

917
00:35:08.857 --> 00:35:11.109
- I am cleared
for my driver's license.

918
00:35:11.192 --> 00:35:13.278
- You shouldn't be driving
at all like this.

919
00:35:13.361 --> 00:35:15.780
If you were a patient.
we would have to report you.

920
00:35:15.822 --> 00:35:17.365
- I am not
your fucking patient.

921
00:35:17.449 --> 00:35:18.450
- No. but I cannot let you work

922
00:35:18.533 --> 00:35:19.868
in my emergency department

923
00:35:19.951 --> 00:35:21.703
until you're fully capable
of doing so.

924
00:35:21.786 --> 00:35:23.413
- That is not
your fucking call!

925
00:35:23.496 --> 00:35:24.956
- You're fucking-A right.
that's my call!

926
00:35:24.998 --> 00:35:26.916
I'm trying to protect you
and my patients.

927
00:35:27.000 --> 00:35:28.251
and you know I'm right
about this.

928
00:35:28.335 --> 00:35:29.961
- Oh. "my department."
"my patients."

929
00:35:30.045 --> 00:35:31.463
All you fucking think about
is yourself!

930
00:35:31.546 --> 00:35:32.797
Do you hear yourself?

931
00:35:32.839 --> 00:35:33.798
You didn't rat out Langdon

932
00:35:33.882 --> 00:35:35.342
for stealing fucking drugs.

933
00:35:35.425 --> 00:35:36.968
- No. but I kicked him
out of this department

934
00:35:37.010 --> 00:35:38.845
until he got the appropriate
help that he needs.

935
00:35:38.928 --> 00:35:40.764
and the same goes for you.

936
00:35:40.847 --> 00:35:42.349
You've got until Monday
to let the administration know.

937
00:35:42.432 --> 00:35:43.600
or I will.

938
00:35:49.439 --> 00:35:50.607
[bell dinging]

939
00:35:50.690 --> 00:35:52.484
- I am finished.

940
00:35:52.525 --> 00:35:54.319
Last chart.

941
00:35:54.361 --> 00:35:55.362
[bell dings]

942
00:35:55.445 --> 00:35:56.863
- You and me both.
- Really?

943
00:35:56.946 --> 00:35:58.448
- Is this a thing?
I finished a while ago.

944
00:35:58.531 --> 00:35:59.908
[bell dings]

945
00:35:59.991 --> 00:36:01.785
- I never want to hear
that fucking bell again.

946
00:36:06.373 --> 00:36:07.791
- Where's Dana?
- Not sure.

947
00:36:07.874 --> 00:36:09.334
A bunch of day shift
just headed to the roof

948
00:36:09.376 --> 00:36:10.502
to watch the fireworks.

949
00:36:10.585 --> 00:36:11.836
You want me to call her?

950
00:36:11.878 --> 00:36:13.380
- No. that's OK.

951
00:36:15.256 --> 00:36:16.675
- Yo.

952
00:36:16.758 --> 00:36:18.468
Thanks for your help in there.

953
00:36:20.387 --> 00:36:22.597
Almost out?
- Yep. just about.

954
00:36:24.891 --> 00:36:26.518
Is this where you try
to talk me out of going?

955
00:36:26.601 --> 00:36:27.519
- Me?

956
00:36:27.602 --> 00:36:29.354
No. not a chance.

957
00:36:29.396 --> 00:36:30.522
Why. are you having
second thoughts?

958
00:36:30.605 --> 00:36:31.523
- Nope.
- No?

959
00:36:31.606 --> 00:36:33.191
- Nope.

960
00:36:33.233 --> 00:36:35.193
- Don't have to convince me.

961
00:36:35.235 --> 00:36:36.528
I mean. it is a little strange
the only place

962
00:36:36.569 --> 00:36:38.029
you talked about going
is somewhere

963
00:36:38.113 --> 00:36:39.364
they used to drive buffalo
off a cliff to die.

964
00:36:39.406 --> 00:36:40.657
- Here it comes.
- I looked it up.

965
00:36:40.740 --> 00:36:42.367
and as far
as summer vacations go.

966
00:36:42.409 --> 00:36:44.077
it's not exactly
a holiday hotspot.

967
00:36:44.160 --> 00:36:47.205
I mean. what's in
the fucking gift shop. man?

968
00:36:47.288 --> 00:36:48.415
- It's just one place
I'm going.

969
00:36:48.498 --> 00:36:50.041
- As long as it's not the last.

970
00:36:50.083 --> 00:36:52.210
Don't be pulling a "Thelma
and Louise" out there.

971
00:36:52.252 --> 00:36:54.379
- I am minutes from taking
a three-month vacation.

972
00:36:54.462 --> 00:36:55.922
When's the last time
you took any time off. Jack?

973
00:36:56.005 --> 00:36:57.882
- Yeah. but I've dealt
with my demons.

974
00:36:59.175 --> 00:37:01.720
It's a process.

975
00:37:01.803 --> 00:37:04.472
You want to know why
I never killed myself?

976
00:37:04.556 --> 00:37:07.892
After what I saw.
lived through?

977
00:37:07.934 --> 00:37:11.521
Losing my leg. losing my wife?

978
00:37:12.772 --> 00:37:14.899
Because it comes
for all of us. man.

979
00:37:14.941 --> 00:37:16.067
You and I know it
more than most.

980
00:37:16.151 --> 00:37:17.819
We see it every shift.

981
00:37:17.902 --> 00:37:20.029
but we can't let ourselves
succumb to it.

982
00:37:21.114 --> 00:37:22.949
Yes. life can suck.

983
00:37:24.284 --> 00:37:26.244
It can be unbearable

984
00:37:26.286 --> 00:37:28.079
and--and brutal

985
00:37:28.121 --> 00:37:30.749
and ugly and heartbreaking.

986
00:37:30.832 --> 00:37:34.919
But it's also beautiful--
and hilarious.

987
00:37:35.003 --> 00:37:37.255
And that woman today...

988
00:37:40.300 --> 00:37:41.801
Her baby. they'd both be
in the morgue

989
00:37:41.885 --> 00:37:43.762
if you hadn't been here.

990
00:37:43.803 --> 00:37:45.597
That's us.
That's you and me.

991
00:37:45.638 --> 00:37:48.558
That's what we're here for.

992
00:37:48.641 --> 00:37:51.144
- The most important things
I've ever done in my life

993
00:37:51.227 --> 00:37:53.813
have been in this hospital.

994
00:37:53.897 --> 00:37:56.274
Nothing will ever matter more
than what I've done

995
00:37:56.357 --> 00:37:59.319
in this hospital.
but it is killing me.

996
00:38:00.945 --> 00:38:02.989
You know how they say
that a part of you dies

997
00:38:03.072 --> 00:38:04.616
when you lose someone you love?

998
00:38:04.699 --> 00:38:07.035
I'm not convinced that
a part of you doesn't die

999
00:38:07.118 --> 00:38:09.204
every time you see
a fellow human pass.

1000
00:38:09.287 --> 00:38:13.708
And I've seen
so many people die

1001
00:38:13.792 --> 00:38:16.836
that I feel like it's leaching
something from my soul.

1002
00:38:18.505 --> 00:38:20.507
- Go on a cruise. man.

1003
00:38:22.884 --> 00:38:25.637
Knock off this
helmetless motorcycle shit.

1004
00:38:25.720 --> 00:38:27.764
Yeah. people talk.

1005
00:38:27.806 --> 00:38:29.140
That's death-wish behavior.

1006
00:38:29.182 --> 00:38:30.600
- I'm tired of being
a role model.

1007
00:38:30.642 --> 00:38:32.477
I'm tired of feeling
like you can't get ahead.

1008
00:38:32.560 --> 00:38:34.270
I'm tired of feeling
like I'm drowning every day.

1009
00:38:34.354 --> 00:38:35.522
I'm tired of all of it.

1010
00:38:35.605 --> 00:38:36.773
- You need to get away
for a while.

1011
00:38:36.856 --> 00:38:38.149
and you need to get some help.

1012
00:38:38.233 --> 00:38:41.694
You need this place
as much as it needs you.

1013
00:38:42.862 --> 00:38:45.990
- [breathes deeply]

1014
00:38:46.074 --> 00:38:48.117
Am I fucked up?

1015
00:38:48.201 --> 00:38:49.786
- 100%.

1016
00:38:53.289 --> 00:38:55.458
But nobody works here
as long as you and me

1017
00:38:55.542 --> 00:38:56.626
and doesn't get screwed up.

1018
00:38:56.709 --> 00:38:59.796
You--you gotta find somebody

1019
00:38:59.879 --> 00:39:02.507
to help you dance
through the darkness.

1020
00:39:02.590 --> 00:39:06.511
- [breathes deeply]

1021
00:39:06.594 --> 00:39:08.304
Did you just make that up?

1022
00:39:10.515 --> 00:39:11.850
- Maybe it's a song lyric.
- [laughs]

1023
00:39:11.891 --> 00:39:13.601
- I don't--
maybe my therapist said it.

1024
00:39:13.685 --> 00:39:15.603
I don't know.

1025
00:39:15.687 --> 00:39:18.356
- [sighs]

1026
00:39:18.398 --> 00:39:19.774
- Some dude just pulled up.

1027
00:39:19.858 --> 00:39:21.901
Looks like he blew
half his face off.

1028
00:39:24.737 --> 00:39:26.573
- How can you not love
this place?

1029
00:39:28.950 --> 00:39:32.328
Look. don't make me
look stupid.

1030
00:39:32.412 --> 00:39:34.831
You come back to us
in one piece.

1031
00:39:38.167 --> 00:39:39.544
I'm still your
emergency contact.

1032
00:39:39.627 --> 00:39:42.005
and I do not want
to be contacted.

1033
00:39:44.340 --> 00:39:45.508
All right. night crawlers.

1034
00:39:45.592 --> 00:39:46.718
what the hell's going on
out here?

1035
00:39:46.801 --> 00:39:49.846
[indistinct chatter]

1036
00:39:52.348 --> 00:39:53.600
- 25-year-old man--

1037
00:39:53.683 --> 00:39:54.893
[indistinct] history.

1038
00:39:54.976 --> 00:39:56.227
no meds. no allergies.

1039
00:39:56.311 --> 00:39:59.355
[continues speaking
indistinctly]

1040
00:40:24.297 --> 00:40:25.298
[lock chirps]

1041
00:40:50.198 --> 00:40:52.951
[engine starts]

1042
00:40:52.992 --> 00:40:54.661
[chiming]

1043
00:41:11.511 --> 00:41:14.514
[sobbing]

1044
00:41:22.689 --> 00:41:24.565
<i>- More than 2.000 years ago.</i>

1045
00:41:24.649 --> 00:41:26.734
the Chinese were throwing
bamboo into fire

1046
00:41:26.818 --> 00:41:28.736
to make explosions.

1047
00:41:28.820 --> 00:41:30.279
They went on
to invent gunpowder.

1048
00:41:30.363 --> 00:41:32.532
And boom! The rest is history.

1049
00:41:34.158 --> 00:41:37.161
They had chemicals to get
the different colors. you know?

1050
00:41:37.245 --> 00:41:39.956
Sodium gives you yellow.
strontium gives you red.

1051
00:41:40.039 --> 00:41:43.001
and barium is green.

1052
00:41:43.084 --> 00:41:46.629
Who knew chemistry could be
so damn pretty?

1053
00:41:46.671 --> 00:41:48.172
[booming]

1054
00:41:48.214 --> 00:41:49.966
[chatter. laughter]

1055
00:41:50.049 --> 00:41:52.969
[fireworks popping]

1056
00:41:53.052 --> 00:41:55.972
<i>["America the Beautiful"
playing]</i>

1057
00:41:56.055 --> 00:42:02.937
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1058
00:42:55.615 --> 00:42:57.283
- Hey.
- Hey.

1059
00:42:57.366 --> 00:42:59.744
- I thought you'd left already.
- On my way out.

1060
00:42:59.786 --> 00:43:03.706
- Hey. I'm sorry that
I didn't find the time today

1061
00:43:03.790 --> 00:43:04.874
to have that conversation.

1062
00:43:04.957 --> 00:43:06.209
- Yeah. that's all right.

1063
00:43:06.292 --> 00:43:08.086
Seems like you
didn't really want to.

1064
00:43:08.169 --> 00:43:10.296
- I didn't. [sighs]

1065
00:43:12.465 --> 00:43:13.800
Did you?

1066
00:43:13.883 --> 00:43:16.177
- Uh...

1067
00:43:16.260 --> 00:43:18.930
yeah. actually.

1068
00:43:19.013 --> 00:43:22.058
Look. I'm doing the work.

1069
00:43:22.141 --> 00:43:24.519
I'm--I've been sober 186 days.

1070
00:43:24.602 --> 00:43:26.771
I'm going to meetings.
I'm taking the drug tests.

1071
00:43:26.813 --> 00:43:29.065
- That's good.
- And you're still riding me.

1072
00:43:32.110 --> 00:43:35.446
What would have happened
if I'd paralyzed that guy?

1073
00:43:35.488 --> 00:43:37.115
- I don't know.

1074
00:43:37.156 --> 00:43:38.699
What would have happened
if I hadn't been here today?

1075
00:43:38.783 --> 00:43:40.409
You'd still be
questioning yourself.

1076
00:43:40.451 --> 00:43:42.120
Now you know you can do it.
You're welcome.

1077
00:43:42.203 --> 00:43:43.746
- Oh. so that's--
that's how you teach now?

1078
00:43:43.830 --> 00:43:45.706
- Sometimes.

1079
00:43:45.790 --> 00:43:48.000
- You know who I saw in rehab?

1080
00:43:48.084 --> 00:43:50.670
I saw a bunch of guys
just like you.

1081
00:43:50.753 --> 00:43:51.963
The only difference is.

1082
00:43:52.046 --> 00:43:55.133
they've accepted
that they need help.

1083
00:43:55.174 --> 00:43:57.135
I think you're afraid
to admit that

1084
00:43:57.218 --> 00:43:59.804
the mighty Dr. Robinavitch
isn't perfect.

1085
00:43:59.887 --> 00:44:01.848
- Oh. I never claimed
to be perfect.

1086
00:44:01.931 --> 00:44:05.143
- No. but you expect it
of yourself.

1087
00:44:05.184 --> 00:44:07.603
and it's not realistic. man.

1088
00:44:07.687 --> 00:44:09.939
How can any of us live up
to your standards

1089
00:44:10.022 --> 00:44:11.732
if you can't even do it?

1090
00:44:13.109 --> 00:44:15.987
You need help. Robby.

1091
00:44:16.070 --> 00:44:17.780
You need help.

1092
00:44:17.864 --> 00:44:20.616
[baby crying]

1093
00:44:20.700 --> 00:44:21.868
- Finished?

1094
00:44:23.035 --> 00:44:25.329
- You don't gotta be honest
with me. man.

1095
00:44:25.413 --> 00:44:27.415
At least be honest
with yourself.

1096
00:44:27.498 --> 00:44:30.543
[baby crying]

1097
00:44:42.930 --> 00:44:45.266
- She is due for a new bottle.

1098
00:44:45.349 --> 00:44:48.102
I was hoping to get her some
formula before I clocked out.

1099
00:44:49.770 --> 00:44:52.064
- I'll stay with her.

1100
00:44:52.148 --> 00:44:53.399
- Thanks.

1101
00:44:55.651 --> 00:44:57.820
- Why are you--will you hit
those lights on your way out?

1102
00:44:57.904 --> 00:45:00.865
- Yep.
- Why are you crying?

1103
00:45:00.907 --> 00:45:03.409
Why are you crying. little one?

1104
00:45:03.492 --> 00:45:06.037
You're OK. You're safe.

1105
00:45:06.078 --> 00:45:08.331
Yeah. you're not alone.

1106
00:45:08.414 --> 00:45:11.417
[baby crying]

1107
00:45:15.254 --> 00:45:17.715
Yeah. you're OK.

1108
00:45:17.798 --> 00:45:21.052
Do you need to be
swaddled again?

1109
00:45:21.093 --> 00:45:22.803
Is that it?

1110
00:45:22.887 --> 00:45:24.722
I can do that. Look.

1111
00:45:24.805 --> 00:45:27.350
Aww.

1112
00:45:27.433 --> 00:45:31.062
I wish somebody
would swaddle me.

1113
00:45:31.145 --> 00:45:33.522
Yes. I do.

1114
00:45:33.606 --> 00:45:35.566
Oh.

1115
00:45:35.650 --> 00:45:37.985
<i>[Rosie Carney's "Thousand"]</i>

1116
00:45:38.069 --> 00:45:41.030
You got off to kind of
a rough start.

1117
00:45:41.113 --> 00:45:44.158
didn't you. little one?

1118
00:45:44.242 --> 00:45:46.244
Yeah. you did.

1119
00:45:46.327 --> 00:45:48.579
<i>- ♪ She is left stuck
on her own ♪</i>

1120
00:45:48.621 --> 00:45:51.249
- Well. that makes two of us.

1121
00:45:51.290 --> 00:45:53.584
<i>- ♪ Dust grows ♪</i>

1122
00:45:53.668 --> 00:45:54.794
- [sighs]

1123
00:45:54.877 --> 00:45:56.879
I got abandoned too.

1124
00:45:56.963 --> 00:46:00.216
<i>- ♪ Can't move. can't grow ♪</i>

1125
00:46:00.299 --> 00:46:02.593
- When I was eight.

1126
00:46:02.635 --> 00:46:06.097
<i>- ♪ When you've fallen
on your knees ♪</i>

1127
00:46:06.180 --> 00:46:11.602
- But I got through
all of that. and so will you.

1128
00:46:11.644 --> 00:46:15.606
I got a good feeling that
you're gonna be just fine.

1129
00:46:15.648 --> 00:46:19.110
Everything's gonna be
just fine.

1130
00:46:19.151 --> 00:46:22.029
You got so many
wonderful things to see

1131
00:46:22.113 --> 00:46:25.241
and so many people to love
ahead of you.

1132
00:46:25.324 --> 00:46:27.410
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1133
00:46:27.493 --> 00:46:32.456
So many wonderful
things to see.

1134
00:46:32.498 --> 00:46:34.583
people to love ahead of you.

1135
00:46:34.667 --> 00:46:37.795
<i>- ♪ To show they really care ♪</i>

1136
00:46:37.878 --> 00:46:40.131
<i>♪ Love. please surround me ♪</i>

1137
00:46:40.172 --> 00:46:43.050
[baby fussing]
- Shh.

1138
00:46:43.134 --> 00:46:47.805
It's OK. It's gonna be OK.

1139
00:46:47.888 --> 00:46:50.391
It's OK.

1140
00:46:50.474 --> 00:46:55.104
<i>- ♪ But a thousand more
to live ♪</i>

1141
00:46:55.187 --> 00:46:58.941
<i>♪ Will it be this way
tomorrow ♪</i>

1142
00:46:59.025 --> 00:47:00.484
<i>♪ I don't know ♪</i>

1143
00:47:00.526 --> 00:47:06.699
<i>♪ But I won't fade ♪</i>

1144
00:47:15.875 --> 00:47:19.962
<i>both:
♪ I want you to know ♪</i>

1145
00:47:20.046 --> 00:47:24.759
♪ That I'm happy for you ♪

1146
00:47:24.842 --> 00:47:28.804
♪ I wish nothing but ♪

1147
00:47:28.888 --> 00:47:33.309
♪ The best for you both ♪

1148
00:47:33.351 --> 00:47:35.519
♪ An older version of me ♪

1149
00:47:35.561 --> 00:47:37.688
♪ Is she perverted like me ♪

1150
00:47:37.772 --> 00:47:42.276
♪ Would she go down on you
in a theater ♪

1151
00:47:42.360 --> 00:47:44.612
♪ Does she speak eloquently ♪

1152
00:47:44.695 --> 00:47:46.822
♪ And would she
have your baby ♪

1153
00:47:46.906 --> 00:47:51.994
♪ I'm sure she'd make
a really excellent mother ♪

1154
00:47:52.078 --> 00:47:53.871
♪ 'Cause the love that you gave
that we made ♪

1155
00:47:53.954 --> 00:47:55.706
♪ Wasn't able
to make it enough ♪

1156
00:47:55.748 --> 00:47:58.876
♪ For you to be open wide ♪

1157
00:47:58.959 --> 00:48:01.212
♪ No ♪

1158
00:48:01.253 --> 00:48:03.547
♪ And every time
you speak her name ♪

1159
00:48:03.631 --> 00:48:04.882
♪ Does she know
how you told me ♪

1160
00:48:04.924 --> 00:48:06.717
♪ You'd hold me
until you died ♪

1161
00:48:06.801 --> 00:48:09.845
♪ Till you died.
but you're still alive ♪

1162
00:48:09.929 --> 00:48:14.350
♪ And I'm here to remind you ♪

1163
00:48:14.433 --> 00:48:16.685
♪ Of the mess that you left ♪

1164
00:48:16.769 --> 00:48:18.896
♪ When you went away ♪

1165
00:48:18.938 --> 00:48:23.526
♪ It's not fair to deny me ♪

1166
00:48:23.609 --> 00:48:27.530
♪ Of the cross I bear
that you gave to me ♪

1167
00:48:27.613 --> 00:48:31.492
♪ You. you. you oughta know ♪

1168
00:48:31.575 --> 00:48:34.495
<i>[Alanis Morissette's
"You Oughta Know" playing]</i>

1169
00:48:34.578 --> 00:48:41.627
<i>♪ ♪</i>
